1
00:00:02,300 --> 00:00:03,970
It looks like you!

2
00:00:04,500 --> 00:00:09,700
- Like me?
- You have that look when you're  collecting insects!

3
00:00:09,700 --> 00:00:11,240
Do I really look like that?

4
00:00:11,240 --> 00:00:12,650
Yes, you do.

5
00:00:12,650 --> 00:00:16,740
Look at those arms!
He'd knock you out with a single punch.

6
00:00:16,740 --> 00:00:18,280
Don't worry!

7
00:00:18,280 --> 00:00:20,780
Gorillas are often thought to be violent

8
00:00:20,780 --> 00:00:24,610
but they are very sensitive and rarely do they attack humans.

9
00:00:25,400 --> 00:00:30,600
Its grip is said to be over 400kg, so you probably
don't want to shake hands.

10
00:00:36,660 --> 00:00:39,570
I'd say about... 20kg.

11
00:00:44,150 --> 00:00:45,800
It doesn't hurt?

12
00:00:45,800 --> 00:00:48,780
Of course, it hurts.

13
00:00:55,830 --> 00:00:57,760
Sir!

14
00:00:57,760 --> 00:01:05,170
- Over here!
- That's a very good drawing.

15
00:01:05,170 --> 00:01:07,410
<i>I wonder</i>

16
00:01:07,410 --> 00:01:11,170
<i>how the two of us look like to strangers.</i>

17
00:01:13,680 --> 00:01:14,690
Shall we go?

18
00:01:14,690 --> 00:01:17,160
<i>Do we look like lovers?</i>

19
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:18,820
<i>Or wife and husband?</i>

20
00:01:19,510 --> 00:01:21,230
<i>No.</i>

21
00:01:21,230 --> 00:01:25,380
<i>We are forbidden to hold hands in public.</i>

22
00:01:27,600 --> 00:01:31,110
<i>We are forbidden to call each other's name in public.</i>

23
00:01:32,320 --> 00:01:34,640
<i>If I lose sight of him,</i>

24
00:01:35,350 --> 00:01:37,050
<i>I may never</i>

25
00:01:37,050 --> 00:01:40,240
<i>see him again.</i>

26
00:01:40,240 --> 00:01:42,190
It's beautiful!

27
00:01:44,100 --> 00:01:45,800
What are you doing?

28
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:48,200
Come chase me when I run away.

29
00:01:48,990 --> 00:01:51,660
I'm not shameless enough to play tag
with someone else's wife.

30
00:01:51,660 --> 00:01:55,710
I can't remember the last time
I came to the beach without the kids.

31
00:01:55,710 --> 00:01:57,430
Play along with me!

32
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:09,700
Are you alright, ma'am?

33
00:02:09,700 --> 00:02:13,300
You're not going to help me up?

34
00:02:20,900 --> 00:02:23,400
You look better when you're in trouble.

35
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:27,400
For the first time, I thought you looked cute.

36
00:02:31,590 --> 00:02:33,310
Pervert.

37
00:02:39,690 --> 00:02:41,900
What are you doing?

38
00:02:41,900 --> 00:02:44,600
You're not afraid?

39
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:49,200
You will lose everything
if your husband finds out.

40
00:02:50,430 --> 00:02:52,140
I am afraid.

41
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:56,960
If I wasn't, I wouldn't be seeing you.

42
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:11,120
I can't believe it!

43
00:03:27,660 --> 00:03:28,670
Hello?

44
00:03:28,670 --> 00:03:30,730
This is Sasamoto.

45
00:03:30,730 --> 00:03:33,550
The fireworks are starting.

46
00:03:33,550 --> 00:03:36,400
Mana and Hina are waiting.

47
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:37,900
Are you going to make it back in time?

48
00:03:37,900 --> 00:03:41,150
Yeah, alright.

49
00:03:41,150 --> 00:03:44,560
<i>Oh, I'm terribly sorry to call you
when you're working.</i>

50
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:47,300
No, I'm the one who should apologize

51
00:03:47,300 --> 00:03:49,430
for pushing my kids on to you.

52
00:03:49,430 --> 00:03:55,320
I'll be right back after i finish work,
if you could stay with them a bit longer.

53
00:03:55,320 --> 00:03:57,340
Sorry about that. Bye.

54
00:04:06,740 --> 00:04:09,810
What's going on, Shun?

55
00:04:09,810 --> 00:04:11,800
Well...

56
00:04:12,630 --> 00:04:14,630
Did you just call me Shun?

57
00:04:14,630 --> 00:04:19,600
Why not? We're not at work.
Hurry, the fireworks are starting!

58
00:04:26,350 --> 00:04:28,050
Oops, sorry.

59
00:04:35,550 --> 00:04:39,390
<i>I thought it might be his wife calling him.</i>

60
00:04:55,720 --> 00:04:57,830
Hello, where are you?

61
00:04:57,830 --> 00:05:00,270
I am by the fountain.

62
00:05:00,270 --> 00:05:02,430
<i>I'm already on the train.</i>

63
00:05:03,120 --> 00:05:04,600
What?

64
00:05:05,760 --> 00:05:08,170
<i>I thought you left me and went home.</i>

65
00:05:08,170 --> 00:05:10,760
I would never leave without telling  you.

66
00:05:11,650 --> 00:05:13,960
<i>Just kidding! Behind you.</i>

67
00:05:17,780 --> 00:05:19,800
<i>You're very mean.</i>

68
00:05:21,470 --> 00:05:23,200
Are you mad?

69
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:26,230
I don't like women who play with men.

70
00:05:26,230 --> 00:05:27,650
I'm sorry.

71
00:05:27,650 --> 00:05:31,760
I just wanted to tease you, to scare you a little.

72
00:05:31,760 --> 00:05:34,670
Hey, you're the one who's mean!

73
00:05:34,670 --> 00:05:38,800
Likewise, I'm sorry.
I walk fast, so this happens often.

74
00:05:41,960 --> 00:05:45,670
- So you leave your wife behind, too?
- I mean...

75
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:56,800
Wait.

76
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:58,510
Hm?

77
00:05:58,510 --> 00:06:02,460
For you. Here.

78
00:06:02,460 --> 00:06:04,650
You're giving this to me?

79
00:06:04,650 --> 00:06:05,680
Take it.

80
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:08,900
Thank you!

81
00:06:10,110 --> 00:06:11,930
Does it look like me?

82
00:06:13,690 --> 00:06:17,150
- You look like this one.
- This one?

83
00:06:17,150 --> 00:06:19,430
So adorable.

84
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:33,300
<i>I saw blue fireworks going up,</i>

85
00:06:33,320 --> 00:06:36,040
<i>in the sky far away.</i>

86
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:40,610
Wow! Amazing.

87
00:06:40,610 --> 00:06:43,680
<i>My husband must be watching the fireworks.</i>

88
00:06:45,470 --> 00:06:47,150
<i>Somewhere else...</i>

89
00:06:47,150 --> 00:06:50,620
<i>His wife may be watching them, too.</i>

90
00:06:53,350 --> 00:06:57,130
<i>A joy so intense that I could throw everything else away...</i>

91
00:06:57,130 --> 00:07:00,960
<i>and an agonizing pain so deep that I need to run away.</i>

92
00:07:01,500 --> 00:07:02,600
Shall we go?

93
00:07:02,600 --> 00:07:05,300
<i>Having an affair is like being on a boat,</i>

94
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:09,660
<i>being tossed in the waves of a storm.</i>

95
00:07:09,660 --> 00:07:13,790
<i>On a boat that will never reach the harbor.</i>

96
00:07:13,790 --> 00:07:20,390
<i>[Hirugao: Love Affairs in the Afternoon]</i>

97
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:38,500
Having heatstroke?

98
00:07:38,500 --> 00:07:40,700
What? I'm fine.

99
00:07:40,700 --> 00:07:42,200
Not you, Mama.

100
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:45,800
Oh, the hamsters? I think they're just bored.

101
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:47,700
They were eating just now.

102
00:07:47,700 --> 00:07:49,700
I see.

103
00:07:49,700 --> 00:07:51,900
<i>It's a typical morning.</i>

104
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:55,800
<i>Nothing has changed these three months.</i>

105
00:07:56,700 --> 00:08:00,100
<i>I still make my husband's lunch.</i>

106
00:08:00,100 --> 00:08:03,700
<i>My husband pays more attention to his hamsters than to me.</i>

107
00:08:03,700 --> 00:08:05,700
<i>How were the fireworks?</i>

108
00:08:05,700 --> 00:08:07,400
<i>They were pretty.</i>

109
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:08,700
<i>What about you, Mama?</i>

110
00:08:08,700 --> 00:08:10,400
How was the cake buffet?

111
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:14,000
Delicious, I stuffed myself.

112
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:17,100
Especially that cheesecake.

113
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:19,600
<i>Just one thing has changed.</i>

114
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:23,600
<i>I have become a better liar.</i>

115
00:08:28,560 --> 00:08:29,500
What are you doing?

116
00:08:29,500 --> 00:08:31,600
The university is on summer break.

117
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:34,310
I have to help out with the chores, too.

118
00:08:34,310 --> 00:08:36,330
Don't worry about it.

119
00:08:36,330 --> 00:08:37,600
You have that report to submit, right?

120
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:40,100
No, I want to do it.

121
00:08:40,100 --> 00:08:41,600
When we have a baby,

122
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:46,100
I'll become a mother, so I need to start being a better wife.

123
00:08:46,100 --> 00:08:47,300
Besides,

124
00:08:47,300 --> 00:08:51,700
I also read from a study that said men's fertility rate increases

125
00:08:51,700 --> 00:08:55,300
when they have higher emotional satisfaction
towards their partner.

126
00:08:55,300 --> 00:08:59,200
I'll cook while the university is on break, okay?

127
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:01,300
It's fine.

128
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:04,000
Let's leave things status quo.

129
00:09:05,900 --> 00:09:07,500
Why?

130
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:09,700
I want you to concentrate on your research.

131
00:09:10,840 --> 00:09:12,730
I'm off to give lessons.

132
00:09:23,600 --> 00:09:24,700
Liar!

133
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:25,700
It's fine, leave it.

134
00:09:25,700 --> 00:09:27,200
You can't call this a journal.

135
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:28,500
Be quiet!

136
00:09:28,500 --> 00:09:29,400
Give it to me!

137
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:33,500
Don't fight. You're going to be late for cram school.

138
00:09:33,500 --> 00:09:36,520
But she made things up, saying that both you and dad
were at the fireworks.

139
00:09:36,520 --> 00:09:37,830
What?

140
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:41,700
Thank you.

141
00:09:41,700 --> 00:09:44,300
Hina you wanted to show me
the fireworks too,  huh?

142
00:09:44,300 --> 00:09:47,200
But dad wasn't even there.

143
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:48,360
Dad, too?

144
00:09:48,360 --> 00:09:52,600
I had to leave to finish up some work during the fireworks.

145
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:56,120
But Sasamoto and his coworker

146
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:58,000
took care of these two.

147
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:01,400
I see. I'll have to thank him, too.

148
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:02,300
Yeah.

149
00:10:02,300 --> 00:10:04,200
Come on, you're going to be late.

150
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:06,100
Okay.

151
00:10:06,100 --> 00:10:09,000
I'll come pick you up if you have to come home late.

152
00:10:10,300 --> 00:10:12,700
Summer school, huh?

153
00:10:12,700 --> 00:10:16,720
Kids nowadays don't even get vacations. I feel bad for them.

154
00:10:16,720 --> 00:10:19,220
They have to, since their friends are going.

155
00:10:19,220 --> 00:10:21,030
But then again...

156
00:10:21,030 --> 00:10:24,200
It's convenient for their mothers, isn't it?

157
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:27,800
They send their kids to cram school

158
00:10:27,800 --> 00:10:29,600
to make time to meet with men.

159
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:33,470
They accept PTA* positions to have a convenient excuse
<i>[*Parent-Teacher Association]</i>

160
00:10:33,470 --> 00:10:36,300
to leave the house.

161
00:10:36,300 --> 00:10:38,510
Women are scary.

162
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:43,100
I'm talking about our magazine column.

163
00:10:43,100 --> 00:10:45,380
Here, your handkerchief.

164
00:10:47,500 --> 00:10:51,700
By the way, can you sweep the floor today?

165
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:54,000
But I sweep it every day.

166
00:10:54,000 --> 00:10:56,100
The floor feels...

167
00:10:56,100 --> 00:11:00,400
kind of sandy.

168
00:11:01,770 --> 00:11:04,950
It's like some sand fell over here...

169
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:09,200
Maybe it's from the beach.

170
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:11,500
Oh, right.

171
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:12,800
Give me your phone.

172
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:13,900
Mine?

173
00:11:13,900 --> 00:11:18,400
I want to change our cell service plan. It'll be cheaper.

174
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:21,000
What's wrong?

175
00:11:22,210 --> 00:11:25,370
I'm the one who pays for it, correct?

176
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:28,800
You're right. Here.

177
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:30,000
I'm going to work.

178
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,800
Have a good day.

179
00:12:01,900 --> 00:12:04,200
My husband has found out.

180
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:05,400
What?

181
00:12:05,400 --> 00:12:06,800
Tomoko.

182
00:12:06,800 --> 00:12:10,900
My wife had your number saved under a female name,

183
00:12:10,900 --> 00:12:13,800
but it was you who answered.

184
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:19,100
Those fireworks were a trap my husband had set up.

185
00:12:20,830 --> 00:12:24,180
I found a GPS tracker on my car,

186
00:12:24,180 --> 00:12:26,200
so I switched to taking a taxi.

187
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:28,700
But he'd already planned for that.

188
00:12:28,700 --> 00:12:31,400
There was another GPS tracker.

189
00:12:44,900 --> 00:12:46,000
Then did he see you...

190
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:47,800
Probably.

191
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:50,200
He took my cell phone away.

192
00:12:50,900 --> 00:12:52,900
Hello.

193
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:58,400
What happened? Both of you look so serious.

194
00:13:16,100 --> 00:13:16,900
Hello?

195
00:13:16,900 --> 00:13:20,500
How is your new work coming along?

196
00:13:20,500 --> 00:13:22,000
I'm working on it now.

197
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:26,000
<i>I can't wait to see your work.</i>

198
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:31,540
It's my own fault.

199
00:13:31,540 --> 00:13:35,770
I broke my own rule about going on a date on weekends.

200
00:13:35,770 --> 00:13:38,700
And because of that...

201
00:13:39,570 --> 00:13:40,760
What do you think

202
00:13:40,760 --> 00:13:42,900
your husband plans to do?

203
00:13:42,900 --> 00:13:44,800
He's quite egotistical.

204
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:47,100
He won't forgive anyone

205
00:13:47,100 --> 00:13:49,100
who takes his possessions.

206
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:52,900
Then, will he ask for a divorce?

207
00:13:52,900 --> 00:13:54,000
Even if he does,

208
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:56,100
I won't agree to it.

209
00:13:56,100 --> 00:13:57,500
I can't make...

210
00:13:57,500 --> 00:14:00,800
my daughters suffer.

211
00:14:00,800 --> 00:14:05,000
You should be ready for when your husband finds out, too.

212
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:06,000
Be ready?

213
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:08,100
Either completely deny it...

214
00:14:08,100 --> 00:14:09,600
or accept it...

215
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:11,510
and apologize profusely.

216
00:14:11,510 --> 00:14:13,590
I...

217
00:14:16,500 --> 00:14:18,200
might leave my home.

218
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:21,000
It's not wise to get a divorce.

219
00:14:22,500 --> 00:14:25,300
If your husband starts suspecting,
you should break up with your lover.

220
00:14:25,300 --> 00:14:27,300
But I feel like I am lying to both of them.

221
00:14:27,300 --> 00:14:29,000
Stop trying to play the damsel in distress.

222
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:32,600
A woman is always fast to try to leave her marriage,

223
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:39,900
but an affair to a man is just a game. It doesn't matter
how deep he's into it. He won't leave his family for you.

224
00:14:42,140 --> 00:14:44,310
I guess...

225
00:14:45,020 --> 00:14:47,200
I can be relieved, then.

226
00:14:47,890 --> 00:14:49,510
I think...

227
00:14:50,220 --> 00:14:53,210
my husband is in love with someone.

228
00:14:53,220 --> 00:14:55,260
It's just my guess.

229
00:14:55,260 --> 00:14:57,400
Is it a physical relationship?

230
00:14:57,400 --> 00:14:59,000
About that...

231
00:15:00,480 --> 00:15:02,250
I don't think so.

232
00:15:02,250 --> 00:15:06,000
My husband is a very serious and conscientious person.

233
00:15:07,060 --> 00:15:11,090
But he just seems distracted,
like he's thinking about another woman.

234
00:15:12,700 --> 00:15:15,000
Do you know who she is?

235
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,000
Not yet.

236
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:20,760
If you don't want a divorce, you shouldn't start hunting him.

237
00:15:20,760 --> 00:15:22,600
So I should pretend not to notice anything?

238
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:27,300
A man will start justifying his actions
if you corner him too much.

239
00:15:27,300 --> 00:15:33,160
Pretend that you didn't notice anything for a while
and be nicer to him.

240
00:15:33,200 --> 00:15:37,600
I promise that he'll come back to you.

241
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:41,600
You're right.

242
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:43,640
He loves me so much...

243
00:15:43,640 --> 00:15:47,200
and he promised we would be together forever.

244
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:50,700
You're showing off?

245
00:15:50,700 --> 00:15:53,680
I mean, we've been together since we were students.

246
00:15:53,680 --> 00:15:58,600
I can't imagine my life without him.

247
00:15:58,600 --> 00:16:00,600
Is your husband a researcher, too?

248
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:03,400
Not really, he's a teacher.

249
00:16:04,600 --> 00:16:07,800
My husband probably has his complaints.

250
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:12,800
He wanted to stay at the research lab,
but I was the one who remained instead.

251
00:16:12,800 --> 00:16:17,580
I use my maiden name for work.

252
00:16:18,300 --> 00:16:23,400
But today I'm going to try to cook for him.

253
00:16:23,400 --> 00:16:24,900
You're trying?

254
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:26,500
I'll try.

255
00:16:26,500 --> 00:16:29,500
Do you want to put your groceries in the refrigerator?

256
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:30,300
Is that alright?

257
00:16:30,300 --> 00:16:31,100
Of course.

258
00:16:31,100 --> 00:16:34,300
Thank you so much.

259
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:23,400
I'm sorry, I'm going home.

260
00:17:24,340 --> 00:17:26,320
Sawa, what happened?

261
00:17:26,320 --> 00:17:30,900
- What's wrong?
- I don't know.

262
00:17:34,800 --> 00:17:36,000
Can i put this in, too?

263
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:37,700
Go ahead.

264
00:17:43,900 --> 00:17:45,800
Noriko...

265
00:17:45,800 --> 00:17:48,800
So sorry, but I have something urgent to take care of.

266
00:17:48,800 --> 00:17:49,600
What?

267
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:52,800
I'm sorry, but please go home today.

268
00:17:57,100 --> 00:17:59,100
